1.title: Prehistory in the Making
1.plot: Investigating a meteorite crash site near their homes, youthful dinosaur enthusiasts Max, Rex and Zoe stumble upon an unexpected chance to put their paleontology skills to the test.

2.title: Battle at the Pyramids
2.plot: The D-Kids learn of additional dinosaur cards, this time bearing the symbols on Rex and Zoe's tablets.

3.title: Tanks a LOT!
3.plot: Max's father embarks on a scholarly visit to a London museum where history comes to life--literally. The D-Team receives urgent news that the Alpha Gang has already infiltrated the museum, where a real-life Saichania roams free. Max, Rex and Zoe find they still have much to learn from their dinosaur partners as they face their cunning enemies in a full-blown dinosaur battle, with the Saichania's fate hanging in the balance.

4.title: Bungle in the Jungle
4.plot: Max's father embarks on a scholarly visit to a London museum where history comes to life--literally.

5.title: Rubble Trouble
5.plot: Friends' tempers flare when Rex's prized ammonite is broken on a fossil dig. The D-Team remains at odds with one another, even when a dinosaur appearance calls them to China. Only when a cave-in at the Great Wall leaves Zoe trapped underground do these young friends realize that the great walls which have arisen between them put them all in peril.

6.title: Don't Mess with Maiasaura
6.plot: When Max's mother goes out of town, Zoe finds herself trying to keep the house in order and the boys out of trouble. Insisting they have no need for mothering, Max and Rex ditch Zoe and head off to the Swiss Alps, the location of the most recent dinosaur sighting. They are surprised to find the Maiasaura is protecting her egg and not budging, even withstanding the Alpha Gangs attacks. Zoe is able to calm the Maiasaura down and teach the boys what mothering is all about.

7.title: A Game Show Showdown
7.plot: When the popular quiz show Gobble Gobble Brain Stompers airs a dinosaur trivia competition, the D-Team and the Alpha Gang can't wait to put each others' knowledge to the test. The game heats up when a Utahsaurus appears at the television studio, spreading mayhem from set to set. Can the D-Team win the prize money and get the dinosaur -- or will the Alpha Gang come out on top?

8.title: Maui Owie
8.plot: The D-Team is excited to learn that the latest dinosaur sighting is in the beautiful islands of Hawaii. As soon as they arrive Chomp befriends the Styracosaurus -- a distant reptilian relative -- leaving the kids plenty of time to soak up some island sun before heading home with a new dinosaur card. But as quickly as the D-Team starts to enjoy the island paradise, the Alpha Gang arrives, intent on stealing the dinosaur to bolster their own prehistoric posse.

9.title: Dino Snore!
9.plot: An argument between Rex and Max over who's too sensitive and who's too clueless to notice a black hole outside his window is cut short when an Ankylosaurus is discovered in a subway station in Tokyo. Confronted by the Alpha Gang and their dinosaur troops, the D-Team must work together to collect the next dinosaur card. However, Rex and Ace end up separated from the group. Can they reunite with the D-Team and prevent the Alpha Gang from claiming the Ankylosaurus?

10.title: Downtown Runaround
10.plot: When Zoe makes the mistake of using Reese's favorite scarf to dress up Paris, she resolves to replace it with a cheap knockoff before Reese notices. Zoe tricks Max and Rex into letting her tag along to the mall by telling them she's looking for dinosaur collectibles. All are surprised to come across a large collection of dinosaur cards and end up in a race across Japan to keep it from falling into the hands of the Alpha Gang.

11.title: Alpha Bets It All
11.plot: The members of the Alpha Gang are in the right place at the right time when a Suchomimus appears on the shores of Monaco. The D-Team arrive to capture the Suchomimus, but before they can, the fishermen suspect the D-Team has something to do with the dinosaur and all their missing fish.

12.title: Alpha's Zeta Point
12.plot: In pursuit of a Ceratosaurus, the D-Team heads to Zeta Point -- and are surprised to discover that Zeta Point is the Alpha Gang's headquarters! The Alpha Gang ends up capturing them and, even worse, they get their hands on Chomp, Ace and Paris.

13.title: Escape from Zeta Point
13.plot: After being captured by the Alpha Gang, the D-Team plots their escape. Lucky for them, Dr. Spike Taylor comes to their rescue. Can the D-Team claim the Ceratosaurus, reclaim Horny and escape the Alpha Gang's base?

14.title: Child's Play
14.plot: An unusual Pachycephalosaurus with rainbow luster beaming from its head has been spotted in Rome. Dr. Z recognizes it as his superpowered hatchling and decides to reclaim it by himself, and the D-Team tries to intervene. However, this Pachycephalosaurus not only has devastating power but also extraordinary speed . . .

15.title: Volcanic Panic
15.plot: While the D-Team are enjoying their vacation in the Canadian Arctic Archipelago, an Acrocanthosaurus has been discovered. The D-Team and the Alpha Gang chase it to an active volcano in the ocean. Will the volcano erupt before they can collect the Acrocanthosaurus card?

imdb.plot outline: Max Taylor is the son of paleontologist Dr. Spike Taylor and is a fan of dinosaurs. Upon falling out of bed one morning, he sees something crashing into the woods. With his friends/fellow D-Team members Rex Owen and Zoe Drake, they find a strange stone and an egg-shaped capsule containing a Triceratops card. When Max rubs a lightning-marked stone and the Triceratops card, the card turns into a real Triceratops. When he rubs it again, it turns back into a card. The third time it happens, the Triceratops appears as a hatchling and Max names it Chomp. Max, Rex, and Zoe soon learn that the dinosaurs are being hunted by the Alpha Gang. Led by Dr. Z and consisting of Ursula, Zander, Ed, Seth, Dr. Z's maid Helga, and Dr. Z's grandchildren Laura and Rod, the Alpha Gang is out to capture Dinosaur Cards in Dr. Z's plot to become the Dinosaur King. When Rex receives a Carnotaurus named Ace and Zoe receives a Parasaurolophus named Paris, the D-Team competes with the Alpha Gang to get to the Dinosaur Cards first in locations around the world.
